						<summary>

						<p>This is a mutilated inscription with the introduction <hi rend="italic">Tirumagaḷpōla</hi> etc. It records a gift of sheep for a perpetual lamp in the temple of Mūlasthānattu-Paramasvāmi by Kuḷattuḻāṉ, a resident of Kuśappāḍi in Tirumuṉaippāḍi-Muḍiyūrnāḍu.</p>						

